<section id="gettingstarted_queryexplorerview">
	<title>Query Explorer View</title>

	<section id="gettingstarted_queryexplorerview_open">
		<title>Opening Query Explorer View</title>

		<para>
			Query Explorer View provides functions of easily checking outline of Query mapping xml defined by project
			and whether Query ID is in use or duplication through icon.
		</para>
		<para>
			Query Explorer View opens automatically when opening Anyframe Query Manager Perspective and
			you can also open it through the following ways.			
		</para>
		<itemizedlist>
			<listitem>
				<para>
					<emphasis role="bold">Opening on Eclipse menu</emphasis>
				</para>
				<para>
					Select  Query Navigator at "Window > Show View > Other..."
				</para>

				<mediaobject>
					<imageobject>
						<imagedata fileref="../image/GettingStarted/explorer-showview.png"
							align="center" />
					</imageobject>
				</mediaobject>
			</listitem>
		</itemizedlist>
	</section>

	<section id="gettingstarted_queryexplorerview_setting">
		<title>Query Explorer View composition</title>

		<para>
			Query Explorer View is composed of the following components.</para>

		<mediaobject>
			<imageobject>
				<imagedata fileref="../image/GettingStarted/perspective-querymanager.png"
					align="center" />
			</imageobject>
		</mediaobject>

		<itemizedlist>
			<listitem>
				<para>
					<emphasis role="bold">Query ID Tree</emphasis>
				</para>
				<para>
					Among Query mapping XML files of the project where Query Manager Nature is defined,
					files registered at Property is shown in tree format.				
				</para>
				<para>
					You can check whether each Query ID is used or duplicated at DAO class.				
				</para>
				<table>
				<title>Query ID Icon</title>
					<tgroup cols="2">
						<colspec colnum="1" colname="col1" colwidth="1*" />
						<colspec colnum="2" colname="col2" colwidth="3*" />
						<thead>
							<row>
								<entry align="center">Icon</entry>
								<entry align="center">Description</entry>
							</row>
						</thead>
						<tbody>
							<row>
								<entry>
									<mediaobject>
										<imageobject>
											<imagedata fileref="../image/GettingStarted/explorer_tag_blue.png"
												align="center" />
										</imageobject>
									</mediaobject>
								</entry>
								<entry>Query ID in use</entry>
							</row>
							<row>
								<entry>
									<mediaobject>
										<imageobject>
											<imagedata fileref="../image/GettingStarted/explorer_tag_dark.png"
												align="center" />
										</imageobject>
									</mediaobject>
								</entry>
								<entry>Query ID not in use</entry>
							</row>
							<row>
								<entry>
									<mediaobject>
										<imageobject>
											<imagedata fileref="../image/GettingStarted/explorer_tag_blue_duplicate.png"
												align="center" />
										</imageobject>
									</mediaobject>
								</entry>
								<entry>Query ID in use and duplication</entry>
							</row>
							<row>
								<entry>
									<mediaobject>
										<imageobject>
											<imagedata fileref="../image/GettingStarted/explorer_tag_dark_duplicate.png"
												align="center" />
										</imageobject>
									</mediaobject>
								</entry>
								<entry>Query ID not in use but in duplication</entry>
							</row>
						</tbody>
					</tgroup>
				</table>
			</listitem>
			<listitem>
				<para>
					<emphasis role="bold">Query Statement</emphasis>
				</para>
				<para>
					If you select ID in the Query ID tree, you can see the query statement of the ID.			
				</para>
			</listitem>
			<listitem>
				<para>
					<emphasis role="bold">Link with Editor</emphasis>
				</para>
				<para>
					The location of the open Query mapping file is shown in Query ID Tree.		
				</para>
			</listitem>
		</itemizedlist>
	</section>
</section>
